{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:55:56.909Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Top-k and top-p (nucleus) sampling truncate the vocabulary before drawing the next token, preventing unlikely tokens from being selected while preserving more diversity than pure greedy decoding. They are standard companions to temperature in agent APIs and local inference servers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Top-k keeps only the k highest-probability tokens. Top-p keeps the smallest set whose cumulative probability exceeds p (nucleus sampling). Providers may expose one or both; OpenAI documents top_p; many open stacks expose top_k via llama.cpp or vLLM."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without truncation, a flat distribution (high temperature) can sample garbage tokens that break JSON. Nucleus sampling adapts the candidate set size to context—tight when one token dominates, wider when uncertain."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Conceptual comparison"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Top-k",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — fixed cap on candidates; simple but ignores distribution shape"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Top-p",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — dynamic cap; drops long tail of low-probability tokens"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "resp = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Name three colors.\"}],\n    temperature=0.8,\n    top_p=0.9,  # nucleus: keep ~90% probability mass\n    max_tokens=60,\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# llama.cpp server example\ncurl http://localhost:8080/completion -d '{\n  \"prompt\": \"List tools an agent might use:\",\n  \"temperature\": 0.7,\n  \"top_k\": 40,\n  \"top_p\": 0.95\n}'"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use top_p 0.9–1.0 with moderate temperature for natural language. Lower top_p (0.5–0.8) further constrains outputs when temperature must stay higher for policy reasons."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tuning temperature and top_p aggressively at the same time without A/B tests"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming OpenAI exposes top_k on all models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Using nucleus sampling without temperature on malformed logits"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Start with defaults (top_p=1, temp=0.2) for tool agents; adjust one knob at a time"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document effective settings per model—Llama and GPT differ"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Top-k and top-p limit which tokens can be sampled"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Nucleus (top-p) adapts candidate count to uncertainty"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Combine with low temperature for structured agent outputs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Local engines often expose more sampling flags than hosted APIs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
